            <fr:title text="monadic functors are conservative and faithful">monadic functors are conservative and faithful</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Given a <fr:link href="/forest/ualg-000A/" title="monadic functor" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/ualg-000A/" display-uri="ualg-000A" type="local">monadic functor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F(f)]]></fr:tex> is an isomorphism, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is too.
</html:p>
  
    
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/forest/trebor/" title="Trebor" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/trebor/" display-uri="trebor" type="local">Trebor</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>27</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>
    It suffices to consider the case where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is the projection functor from the <fr:link href="/forest/ualg-0002/" title="algebra of a monad" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/ualg-0002/" display-uri="ualg-0002" type="local">Eilenberg–Moore category</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}^M]]></fr:tex>. Morphisms between <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[MX \to  X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[MY \to  Y]]></fr:tex> are given by morphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> satisfying some condition. Therefore the functor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> must be faithful. Furthermore, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is an isomorphism, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}]]></fr:tex> also satisfy the condition (that is, the square made by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f, Mf]]></fr:tex> and the two algebra maps commute). Therefore <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> must be conservative.
  </html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
  
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
