            <fr:title text="monad on a category">monad on a category</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  A <html:strong>monad</html:strong> on a category <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> is a functor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M : \mathcal {C} \to  \mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> equipped with natural transformations <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta  : \textrm {Id} \to  M]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu  : M \mathbin {\circ } M \to  M]]></fr:tex> satisfying identity and associativity laws. In an unbiased way, we have a family of natural transformations <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M^n \to  M]]></fr:tex> with associativity.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
  In short, it is a monoid in the category of endofunctors equipped with composition as the monoidal product.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
